{"lemma":"رِبْقِ","slug":"رِبْقِ","root":"ر.ب.ق","root_slug":"ر-ب-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ب-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14576","n14579"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%92%D9%82%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14576","headword_ar":"ربّق","root":"rbq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He prepared the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arobaAq","text_ar":"اَرْبَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riboqN","text_ar":"رِبْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ram~aditi AlD~aA^onu farab~qo rab~qo","text_ar":"رَمَّدِتِ الضَّاْنُ فَرَبّقْ رَبّقْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i.e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The ewes have secreted milk in their udders: therefore"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prepare thou the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arobaAq","text_ar":"اَرْبَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prepare thou the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArbAq","text_ar":"ارباق"},{"kind":"text","text":": for they will bring forth soon: (S, K:) because they [begin to] secrete milk in their udders"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^osi Alwaladi","text_ar":"رَاْسِ الوَلَدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. at the time of bringing forth, or when about to produce the young]. (S.) It is not thus in the case of she-goats: therefore, (S,) in the case of these, one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ran~qo","text_ar":"رَنّقْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) meaning “ wait thou: ” because they show sings of pregnancy in the state of their udders, and bring forth after some length of time: and [in the case of these] one says also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ram~iqo","text_ar":"رَمِّقْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K. [See arts."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rmq","text_ar":"رمق"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rnq","text_ar":"رنق"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b2-  One also says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~aqa A^avonaA='a AlHaboli","text_ar":"رَبَّقَ اَثْنَا=ءَ الحَبْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made loops in the middle of the rope to put upon the necks of the young lambs"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kids."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vnY","text_ar":"ثنى"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-  See also 1. ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~aqotu AlkalaAma","text_ar":"رَبَّقْتُ الكَلَامَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I interlarded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"embel-lished, the speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discourse, with falsehood;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ram~aqotuhu","text_ar":"رَمَّقْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laf~aqotu bayonahu","text_ar":"لَفَّقْتُ بَيْنَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (JK;) [or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laf~aqotuhu","text_ar":"لَفَّقْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarobiyqu AlkalaAmi","text_ar":"تَرْبِيقُ الكَلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"talofiyquhu","text_ar":"تَلْفِيقُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Ibn-'Abbád, K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taromiyquhu","text_ar":"تَرْمِيقُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ibn-'Abbád.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n14579","headword_ar":"رِبْقٌ","root":"rbq","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cord having in it a number of loops wherewith lambs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kids, are tied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made fast; any one of which loops is termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riboqapN","text_ar":"رِبْقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raboqapN","text_ar":"رَبْقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cord which is doubled in the form of a ring, into which is put the head of a sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goat, and which is then tied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made fast:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so, says Az, I have heard from the Arabs of the desert of Benoo-Temeem: (TA:) pl. [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribaAqN","text_ar":"رِبَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ribaqN","text_ar":"رِبَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arobaAqN","text_ar":"اَرْبَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) ―         -b2-  Hence, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaEa","text_ar":"خَلَعَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_isolaAmi mino Eunuqihi","text_ar":"الاـِسْلَامِ مِنْ عُنُقِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riboqapa","text_ar":"رِبْقَةَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, TA,) occurring in a trad., (S,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cast off the tie of El-Islám,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA,) with which he had bound himself, (TA,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from his neck."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (Msb, TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaEa","text_ar":"خَلَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lakumu AlEahodu maA lamo taA^okuluwA Alr~ibaAqa","text_ar":"لَكُمُ العَهْدُ مَا لَمْ تَاْكُلُوا الرِّبَاقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", also occurring in a trad., (S,) meaning (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The covenant is yours"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as long as ye sever not the tie with which ye are bound;"},{"kind":"text","text":"this tie being likened to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riboq","text_ar":"رِبْق"},{"kind":"text","text":"upon the necks of lambs or kids; and the severing thereof, to the beast's eating its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riboq","text_ar":"رِبْق"},{"kind":"text","text":", and severing it; for thereby the beast becomes free from the tie. (TA.) And in a trad. of 'Omar,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huj~uwA biAl*~ur~iy~api laA taA^okuluwA A^arozaAqahaA wata*aruwA A^arobaAqahaA fiY","text_ar":"حُجُّوا بِالذُّرِّيَّةِ لَا تَاْكُلُوا اَرْزَاقَهَا وَتَذَرُوا اَرْبَاقَهَا فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEonaAqihaA","text_ar":"اَعْنَاقِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Perform ye the pilgrimage with the women: devour not their means of subsistence, while ye leave their ties upon their necks"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: he likens the obligations imposed upon them to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArbAq","text_ar":"ارباق"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) One says also, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hal~a riboqatahu","text_ar":"حَلَّ رِبْقَتَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He removed from him his anxiety:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTaEa riboqatahu","text_ar":"قَطَعَ رِبْقَتَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}